# JS Array Iterators Map, Filter & Reduce

Use declarative programming styles:

```javascript
const items = [12, 45, 78, 90];
// Map
const doubleValues = items.map(x => x * 2);
// Filter
const filtered = items.filter(x => x > 50);
// Reduce
const summation = items.reduce((acc, curr) => acc + curr, 0);
```

### Key Concepts
- **Immutable output**: Functions generate new instances rather than mutating initial state.
- **Callback functions**: Lambda triggers inside array evaluation loop.

